<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> element identifies the defining instance of a term. The paragraph, definition list group, or section containing the <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> should also contain the definition. Styled with italic and semi-bold (<code>font-weight: 500</code>) to distinguish it from regular italic text like <a href="/docs/elements/native/em/"><code>&lt;em&gt;</code></a> or <a href="/docs/elements/native/i/"><code>&lt;i&gt;</code></a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>First use of technical terms:</strong> Define jargon when introduced</li>
      <li><strong>Glossary entries:</strong> Mark terms in a glossary (inside <a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a>)</li>
      <li><strong>Educational content:</strong> Introduce new vocabulary or concepts</li>
      <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Define product-specific terminology</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>When NOT to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>For emphasis &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/em/"><code>&lt;em&gt;</code></a> or <a href="/docs/elements/native/strong/"><code>&lt;strong&gt;</code></a></li>
      <li>For repeated uses of the term &mdash; only mark the defining instance</li>
      <li>For abbreviations alone &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/abbr/"><code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code></a> (but wrap <code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code> inside <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> when first defining it)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/dfn-examples.html" url="dfn-examples.html" title="Definition examples" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic definition">{{ basicDfnCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="With abbreviation">{{ dfnWithAbbrCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="With ID for linking">{{ dfnWithIdCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="In a definition list">{{ dfnInDlCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Title Attribute</h2>
    <p>When the content of <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> differs from the term being defined (e.g., an abbreviation), use <code>title</code> to specify the full term:</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="dfn with title">{{ dfnWithTitleCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Reference</h2>
    <code-block language="css" label="dfn CSS">{{ dfnCssCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p>The semi-bold weight (<code>500</code>) distinguishes <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> from <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> (which is just italic) and <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> (also just italic).</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Some screen readers announce defined terms, helping users identify definitions</li>
      <li>The surrounding paragraph should contain the actual definition</li>
      <li>Adding an <code>id</code> enables linking from other occurrences back to the definition</li>
      <li>Search engines can use <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> to extract term-definition pairs</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/abbr/"><code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code></a> &mdash; For abbreviations (often used inside <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code>)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Definition lists for glossaries</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Definition term (wraps <code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code> in glossary patterns)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/a/"><code>&lt;a&gt;</code></a> &mdash; For linking back to definitions via <code>id</code></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/em/"><code>&lt;em&gt;</code></a> &mdash; For emphasis (not definitions)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
